Dear Clare,

Thanks for the information, and pleased to meet you via email :)

Looking through the call I would agree that the Smart Communities theme is the most relevant. Broadly speaking, our research covers the impact of environmental change on the water cycle - this includes looking at extremes (floods/droughts) as well as latent threats to water resources arising from processes such as population growth, climate change, and urbanisation.

I'm currently involved in two projects in Africa - Pathways (led by Majid) and TWIGA (an EU-H2020 innovation project - http://twiga-h2020.eu/). So, we have a number of potential partners on the Africa side, e.g.

University of Ghana - main African academic partner on Pathways
People's Dialogue - NGO working in Accra and other cities
iLabAfrica @ Strathmore University (Nairobi, but with continental scope)
Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST)

I'm meeting my supervisor (Dr Wouter Buytaert - CC'd) to discuss some ideas, and will get in touch afterwards. 

Thanks,
Simon

